def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    if axis == 1:
        if key is None:
            keys = obj.columns
        elif isinstance(key, str):
            keys = [key]
        else:
            keys = list(key)

        # Ensure the keys are valid column names
        for k in keys:
            if k not in obj.columns:
                raise KeyError(k)

        groupings = []
        for k in keys:
            ping = Grouping(
                obj.columns,
                obj[k],
                obj=obj,
                name=k,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True,
            )
            groupings.append(ping)

        grouper = BaseGrouper(obj.columns, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
        return grouper, keys, obj
    else:
        group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)
